ism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American women in literature. 0aAfrican American womenxIntellectual life. 0aAfrican Americans in literature. 0aAmerican literaturexAfrican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican literaturexWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aFeminism and literaturexUnited States. 0aFeminism and literaturezUnited States. 0aPsychoanalysis and literaturexUnited States. 0aPsychoanalysis and literaturezUnited States. 0aPsychology in literature. 0aRace in literaturexUnited States. 0aRace in literature. 0aRace relations in literature. 0aWomen and literaturexUnited States. 0aWomen and literaturezUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aAbel, Elizabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChristian, Barbara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoglen, Helene, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520918153?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520918153423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520918153/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles